## Finance Stack Foundations Every Startup Needs

A **finance stack** is the set of cloud-based tools that automate your financial operationsâ€”from recording transactions to producing reports.  
Itâ€™s the digital backbone that replaces a five-person accounting team, running continuously at a fraction of the cost.

### General Ledger and Chart of Accounts
The **general ledger** is the single source of truth for every transaction.  
Tools like **QuickBooks Online**, **Xero**, or **NetSuite** integrate with banks and credit cards to eliminate manual entry.

The **chart of accounts** organizes dataâ€”separating revenue by product, expenses by department, and tracking critical KPIs.  
A clean setup ensures investor-ready reporting as you grow.

### Accounts Payable and Expense Management
Modern tools like **Bill.com** and **Ramp** automate the entire accounts payable workflow:
- Digital invoice capture and approval routing  
- Real-time expense categorization  
- Direct sync with accounting software  

Look for solutions that include:
- Real-time spending controls  
- Mobile receipt capture  
- Virtual cards for recurring software costs  

### Revenue Recognition and Billing
Subscription billing gets complex fast.  
Platforms like **Stripe Billing**, **Chargebee**, or **Recurly** automate:
- Deferred revenue recognition  
- Proration for mid-cycle plan changes  
- Seamless CRM integration for closed deals â†’ invoices â†’ payments  

### Payroll and HRIS Integration
Tools such as **Gusto** or **Rippling** manage payroll, benefits, and compliance automatically, syncing directly with your ledger.  
Integrated HRIS provides full visibility into headcount costs and departmental budgets.

### Data Warehouse and BI Layer
**Business intelligence tools** like **Looker**, **Tableau**, or **Sigma** consolidate data from your accounting, CRM, and payment systems.  
A **data warehouse** centralizes this information, powering real-time dashboards for metrics like:
- Unit economics  
- Customer lifetime value (LTV)  
- Profitability by channel  

