## Step-by-Step Roadmap to Automate Your Books and Billing

The biggest implementation mistake startups make is **doing everything at once**.  
Use this phased roadmap instead.

### Step 1: Clean Historical Data
Reconcile all accounts, close prior months, and fix categorization issues before migration.  
Key cleanup tasks include:
- Resolving outstanding receivables/payables  
- Balancing your opening balance sheet  
- Removing duplicates and â€œmiscellaneousâ€ transactions  

### Step 2: Implement AP and Corporate Card Automation
Automate payables firstâ€”it delivers the fastest ROI.  
Set up:
- Bank and card integration  
- Mobile receipt capture  
- Approval workflows by department and spend level  

Target: 90% of expenses flow automatically, 10% go through human review.

### Step 3: Connect Revenue Platforms
Integrate your CRM (e.g., HubSpot, Salesforce) with your billing and accounting systems.  
This ensures closed deals trigger invoices, recognized revenue, and proper accounting entries automatically.

### Step 4: Establish a Monthly Close Checklist
Create a standardized **month-end close** procedure.  
Tasks typically include:
- Reconciling balance sheet accounts  
- Reviewing unusual transactions  
- Posting accruals  
- Producing management reports  

With automation, most startups close within **3â€“5 business days**, versus 10â€“15 manually.

