## When to Hire, Outsource, or Stay Lean

The right structure depends on revenue size, transaction complexity, and need for strategic guidance.

### Bookkeeper vs. Automation

| Task | Automation Capability | When You Need a Human |
|------|-----------------------|------------------------|
| Transaction categorization | 90% automated with AI | Complex or new vendors |
| Bank reconciliation | Automatic matching | Investigate exceptions |
| Invoice processing | Automated routing | Vendor disputes |
| Monthly close | Auto-reconciled | Final review & adjustments |

ðŸ’¡ **Best practice:** Use automation for repetitive work, and supplement with a part-time bookkeeper (5â€“10 hrs/month) for review and quality control.

### Controller or Fractional Controller
A controller ensures GAAP compliance, manages the close, and validates accuracy.  
Fractional controllers (20â€“40 hrs/month) are ideal for **$3Mâ€“$15M** revenue businesses needing high-level oversight without the full-time cost.

### FP&A Analyst or Fractional CFO
**FP&A** covers forecasting, budgeting, and financial modeling.  
A **fractional CFO** adds strategic leadershipâ€”helping you evaluate investments, funding options, and profitability levers.  
At Bennett Financials, we often see this become vital around **$2Mâ€“$3M** revenue.

